FBIS4-24618 "drchi105_i_94005" FBIS-CHI-94-105 Daily Report 31 May 1994 East Europe Poland Claims PRC Support for UN Security Council Position Poland Claims PRC Support for UN Security Council Position LD3105094494 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 0900 GMT 31 May 94 LD3105094494 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network Polish BFN [Text] In 1996 Poland will apply for membership of the UN Security Council. Poland wants to become one of the nonpermanent members of the UN Security Council. Sejm Speaker Jozef Oleksy said after his talks with Chinese politicians in Beijing that our country can count on favorable reaction from the People's Republic of China, which is one of the permanent members of the UN Security Council.
